    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Quick &amp; Reilly Inc., the discount brokerage firm in New York, has selected Grey Direct in New York to handle its account, which was at Kirshenbaum &amp; Bond in New York for 19 months until that agency resigned earlier this year. Billings were estimated at $7 million.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>Quick &amp; Reilly Inc., the discount brokerage firm in New York, has selected Grey Direct in New York to handle its account, which was at Kirshenbaum &amp; Bond in New York for 19 months until that agency resigned earlier this year. Billings were estimated at $7 million.</p>
        <p>Russell Nype, director of acquisition marketing for Quick &amp; Reilly, confirmed a report of the appointment this week in Adweek. He said Grey Direct was awarded the account after a three-month review that also included Clarion Direct in Greenwich, Conn., and Rapp Collins Marcoa in New York. A campaign is expected to begin on Nov. 1.  THE MEDIA BUSINESS: ADVERTISING -- ADDENDA</p>
      </block>
